children.subject: Also why are so many seats reserved for new students? How many students who are just entering the school would even be able to enroll in 16B assuming they haven't taken 16A yet? I feel like the reserved seats are copy-pasted from the spring semester 16B which applies differently

history.content:
Hi,

As in the title, I was wondering why it is the case. What would be the rationale behind it?

It does't make too much sense to me because cs majors need them to graduate, but they have even lower priority than at least some undeclared students.

There's no policy to encourage CS majors to do them early (not needed to declare or for most classes), but there are policies against doing them as upper div, which is very counter-intuitive but I don't remember being warned about this.

Could we add some seats for this group?

Thanks!
history.subject: Why does 16b have no reserved seats for upper div cs majors?
